Comment.ss:Data: Contains data for creating a Accounting Journal and submitting for business processing
Required for all transactions. Used to uniquely identify a transaction header. All rows with the same value will be submitted to Workday as one transaction set.

You must use the header key to coordinate the header information throughout the tabs of the spreadsheet. Keep the same header key for each row as you add information in the subsequent tabs. The header key is also required to coordinate multiple child rows that roll up to the same parent row.
Add Only Flag. Indicates that the service is an add only, not an update.

The boolean Create Journal With Errors is supplied to indicate to the processing whether a journal for a ledger company with Alternate Account Sets enabled should be created even if there is no mapping to a proper Alternate Ledger Account.
Reference to an existing Accounting Journal
Accounting Journal Reference ID. This is the Accounting Journal unique identifier

Submit for Approval is a boolean flag indicating if the transaction is to be submitted or saved in draft mode. If this flag is set, the transaction will be submitted, otherwise the transaction is saved in draft.

Round Ledger Amounts allows for automatically balancing rounding differences for the ledger amounts for a multi-currency Journal Entry as long as the following criteria are met: *All Line Company References must match the Company Reference for the Accounting Journal *No Ledger Debit or Ledger Credit Amounts are populated *All journal lines use the same currency rate *All journal lines use the same transaction currency *A Balancing Worktag Reference is not specified for the Accounting Journal
Journal Number. The Journal Number will be automatically generated through the sequencing number configuration.
Reference to an existing Company which holds the asset
Reference to the currency of the company. If entered, this field is not processed on inbound Workday Web Services requests.
Reference to an existing Ledger Type
Reference to the Book Code the Journal is booked to
Reference to an existing Journal Source
This transaction header memo will print on the delivered transaction. It is optional freeform text
This is a freeform text reference that is used to associate this Journal with a record in a third party system
Boolean flag indicating if the journal entry is an adjustment.
Boolean to enable Journal Line Tax Detail Data.
Boolean attribute indicating if the journal entry should create a reversal
Date for which the reversal journal is to be posted.
Reference to an existing instance of Currency Rate Type
Encapsulating element containing Tax Details data
Row # is for Workday's internal use only. Customers should not populate this column.
Optional line order. If specified, lines will be sorted by this value when displayed and when invoice is printed.

The company for the line for intercompany journals.If field is left blank, it will default to the same company as the header company. For non-intercompany journals this field should be left blank or have the same value as the header company. For beginning balance journal loads, this field should always be blank or the same as the header company. For journals that are intercompany beginning balances, the other company should only be referenced as an intercompany affiliate worktag.
Reference to an existing Ledger Account. The Ledger Account reference is a 2 part reference ID, composed of the Ledger Account ID and the Reference ID for the Ledger Account Set it is organized into.
Contains a unique identifier for an instance of a parent object

Alternate Ledger Account (ALA) provides the ability, when Alternate Account Set is enabled for the header company, to override the account to which the Ledger Account is mapped by the Alternate Account Set Mapping rules. I.E. - if the Ledger Account is 1000 Cash, and the mapping rules map the journal to the 1100 Alternate Cash account, setting the ALA to 1200: Other Cash Account will cause the journal to use Other Cash rather than Alternate Cash.
Contains a unique identifier for an instance of a parent object
Reference to the currency of the company. If entered, this field is not processed on inbound Workday Web Services requests.
This is a freeform text reference that is used to associate this Journal with a record in a third party system
Budget Date for the Journal Line. It is required if the View Budget Date flag is set to true for the Ledger.
Enter the Cost Center Reference ID
Enter Cash Code Reference ID (WMG_CF_PURCHASE - For purchase WMG_CF_SALE For Sale)

For expense report and supplier invoice transactions tied to a capital project worktag, Workday creates special accounting to appropriately debit the Work in Progress account, while also recording the amount as a debit into the Spend account. This is necessary to reflect correct amounts for the purposes of Budget Checking/Reporting, and any other custom spend reports.
The date the transaction occurred for the manual journal with direct tax.
The reference id value for the tax type.
The transaction taxable amount basis for the tax amount entered in the debit/credit amount of the journal line with tax.
The reference id value for the tax code.
The reference id value for the tax rate.
The reference id value of the tax applicability.
The reference id value for the tax recoverability.
The reference id value for the supplier.
The name of the customer or supplier if not defined within Workday.
The address for the customer or supplier if not defined within Workday.
The tax id for the customer or supplier if not defined within Workday.
